The paper focuses on the interaction between humans and robots, specifically on the mental models that operators have of remote robots. This topic is closely related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and robotics (cs.RO). The proposed solution involves a conversational assistant, which is an application of natural language processing (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of mental model clarity on human-machine teaming, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HCI) and systems and control (cs.SY).
